- "garden" is a metaphor for a project;
- "latest accuracy" refers to the most recent accuracy metric from the model's performance evaluation.

- 'Largest teams' refers to the number of unique users who have edited the project;
- 'Most models' refers to the number of unique models associated with the project;
- 'Most data sets' refers to the number of unique data sets linked to the project;
- 'Highest budgets' refers to the allocated budget for the project.

- "data set accesses" refer to the number of times a data set has been accessed or queried;
- "total access count" is the sum of all access events for all data sets associated with a project;
- The projects are ranked in descending order of their total access counts, with the most accessed projects appearing first.

- A project can have multiple models;
- Each model has an evaluation date that indicates when the latest evaluation was performed;
- The query aims to provide a summary of project performance based on the number of models and their latest evaluations.

- "tallest sunflowers" refers to projects with the highest model accuracy;
- "standing proudly" implies the projects are leading in terms of performance;
- "total budget" is the sum of all allocated funds for a project;
- "number of models" is the count of models associated with a project.

- 'completed' refers to the status of the data preprocessing steps that have been successfully finished;
- 'version >= 1' indicates that the data sets must be of a version 1 or higher;
- 'project_id = 1' specifies the project of interest;
- 'total_execution_duration > 10' ensures that only projects with a total preprocessing time greater than 10 minutes are included.

sql:
SELECT SUM(true_positive) AS true_positives, SUM(false_positive) AS false_positives
FROM confusion_matrices
WHERE version > 1;

